 overall scope of transfer research, and discusses the few previous studies that have laid the groundwork for this approach. The core of the book consists of five empirical studies that use computer classifiers to detect the native-language affiliations of texts written by foreign language learners of English. The results highlight combinations of language features that are the most reliable predictors of learners’ language backgrounds.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEnglish languagexRhetoricxStudy and teaching. 0aLanguage transfer (Language learning) 0aLanguage transfer (Language learning). 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Psycholinguistics.2bisacsh  acomputer classifiers to detect language background.  acrosslinguistic influence in SLA.  acrosslinguistic influence.  adetection-based approach.  alearners’ native-language backgrounds.  atransfer in SLA.  atransfer in language learning.1 aBestgen, Yves, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCastañeda-Jiménez, Gabriela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCrossley, Scott A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCrossley, Scott A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGranger, Sylviane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJarvis, Scott, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJarvis, Scott, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMcNamara, Danielle S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcNamara, Danielle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNielsen, Rasmus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPaquot, Magali, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.lo